          <div
            class="MuiBox-root css-1ldlsmb"
            id="faq-are-hysa-returns-taxable-in-singapore"
          >
            <h2
              class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-h6 css-sylb4b-MuiTypography-root"
            >
              Are HYSA returns taxable in Singapore?
            </h2>
            <p
              class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-body1 css-15njp46-MuiTypography-root"
            >
              No. Interest earned on savings accounts in Singapore is tax-free for individuals. Singapore does not tax personal savings interest, dividend income, or capital gains. This applies to both Singapore citizens and foreigners. However, if you earn interest through a business or corporate account, different rules may apply.
            </p>
            <div
              class="MuiBox-root css-ah5j3r"
            >
              <span
                class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-caption css-1xtvbso-MuiTypography-root"
              >
                Sources
              </span>
              <ul
                class="MuiBox-root css-n1ol3p"
              >
                <li
                  class="MuiBox-root css-1itv5e3"
                >
                  <a
                    class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-inherit MuiLink-root MuiLink-underlineAlways css-byaapg-MuiTypography-root-MuiLink-root"
                    href="https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/what-is-taxable-what-is-not/interest"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    target="_blank"
                  >
                    IRAS — Interest (What Is Taxable, What Is Not)
                    <svg
                      aria-hidden="true"
                      class="MuiSvgIcon-root MuiSvgIcon-fontSizeMedium css-2e2mzl-MuiSvgIcon-root"
                      data-testid="OpenInNewIcon"
