      <div
        class="MuiBox-root css-1ldlsmb"
        id="faq-how-do-i-qualify-for-bonus-interest-rates"
      >
        <h2
          class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-h6 css-sylb4b-MuiTypography-root"
        >
          How do I qualify for bonus interest rates?
        </h2>
        <p
          class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-body1 css-15njp46-MuiTypography-root"
        >
          Each bank has its own set of qualifying criteria. Common requirements include: (1) crediting your monthly salary via GIRO, (2) spending a minimum on the bank's credit card, (3) making at least 3 GIRO bill payments, (4) purchasing an insurance or investment product, (5) maintaining a minimum account balance, and (6) using PayNow or the bank's mobile app. The calculator assumes you meet the criteria for each account. Check each bank's detail page for the exact requirements.
        </p>
        <div
          class="MuiBox-root css-ah5j3r"
        >
          <span
            class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-caption css-1xtvbso-MuiTypography-root"
          >
            Sources
          </span>
          <ul
            class="MuiBox-root css-n1ol3p"
          >
            <li
              class="MuiBox-root css-1itv5e3"
            >
              <a
                class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-inherit MuiLink-root MuiLink-underlineAlways css-byaapg-MuiTypography-root-MuiLink-root"
                href="https://www.dbs.com.sg/personal/support/bank-multiplier-eligible-transactions.html"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                target="_blank"
              >
                DBS Multiplier — Eligible Transactions
                <svg
                  aria-hidden="true"
                  class="MuiSvgIcon-root MuiSvgIcon-fontSizeMedium css-2e2mzl-MuiSvgIcon-root"
